To check the version of libc used by `aarch64-none-linux-gnu-gcc`, you can follow these steps:

1. Open a terminal or command prompt.

2. Run the following command to compile a simple C program that prints the libc version:
```
aarch64-none-linux-gnu-gcc -o check_libc_version -xc - << EOF
#include <stdio.h>
#include <gnu/libc-version.h>

int main() {
    printf("Libc version: %s\n", gnu_get_libc_version());
    return 0;
}
EOF
```

3. After running the above command, you will have an executable file named `check_libc_version`.

4. Now, execute the `check_libc_version` program:
```
./check_libc_version
```

This will display the version of the libc library used by the `aarch64-none-linux-gnu-gcc` toolchain.
